es the interplay between Son Jarocho’s indigenous roots and contemporary role in Mexican and US society. The result is a nuanced portrait of a vital and evolving musical tradition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFolk musiczMexicozSotaventoxHistory and criticism. 0aHarpistszMexicovBiography. 0aMexican AmericansxMusicxHistory and criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aSon Jarocho, Mexican music, Mexican music studies, ethnography of Mexican music, Chicano, Chicano music, Chicano music culture, musicology, ethnomusicology.  afandango.1 aBarradas, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroyles-González, Yolanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFigueroa Hernández, Rafael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Francisco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHernández, Rafael Figueroa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076651640uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32555140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477325575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477325575/original  a978-3-11-076651-6  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  